@startuml
title FIG-21-01. Choosing the Right Security Architecture View
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F5F7FA
  BorderColor #333333
  FontColor #111111
  RoundCorner 10
}
left to right direction
rectangle "Start with the\nsecurity question" as Start #DCEAF7
rectangle "Security context" as Context
rectangle "Trust-boundary view" as Trust
rectangle "Authentication sequence" as Authn
rectangle "Access-authorisation model" as Authz
rectangle "Threat-model DFD\nor attack tree" as Threat
rectangle "Security-control map" as Control
rectangle "Privacy data-flow\nor lifecycle view" as Privacy
rectangle "Audit and monitoring view" as Monitor
rectangle "Clarify asset, audience,\nboundary and decision" as Clarify #FFF2CC
Start --> Context : What is in scope\nand valuable?
Start --> Trust : Where does\ntrust change?
Start --> Authn : How is identity\nestablished?
Start --> Authz : Who may perform\nwhich action?
Start --> Threat : How could an asset\nbe harmed?
Start --> Control : Which controls\naddress the risk?
Start --> Privacy : How is personal\ndata handled?
Start --> Monitor : What must be detected\nand acted upon?
Start --> Clarify : Still unclear?
@enduml
